{"questionId":"11928","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Saloni wants to find a model for the temperature of a bottle of water after she removes it from the fridge. She uses a temperature probe to record the temperature of the water, every 5 minutes.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/e0e3e0c85b8be5fd992a7706300644908ac9f9b7.png\"></p>\n<p>After graphing the data, Saloni believes a suitable model will be</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T = 28 - a{b^t}\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>28</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b \\in {\\mathbb{R}^ + }\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the equation of the least squares exponential regression curve for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"28 - T\">\n  <mn>28</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>T</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/40542682ea13474848eaee6456dd1d2a3977ce3b.png\"><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"28 - T = 22.7{\\left( {0.925} \\right)^t}\">\n  <mn>28</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>T</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>22.7</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>0.925</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11928","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.21b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the equation of the least squares exponential regression curve for 28 − T .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.13—Non-linear regression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}